  "name": "CRC OS link from the tumor growth-rate constant k_g (Weibull PH)",
  "description": "Parametric proportional-hazards link to OS driven by the tumor GROWTH-RATE CONSTANT k_g (post-nadir regrowth) rather than the early week-8 change. S(t) = exp(-(t/scale)^shape * exp(beta * k_g)); a faster-regrowing tumor raises the hazard. Non-default, tail-sensitive alternative to the CRC week-8 link (structure.default=false), reached via survival_link=. A model with no regrowth (k_g undefined) maps to the baseline hazard. Population/trial-level only; values illustrative and unverified.",
